{
  "texts": [
    "Claude-3 shows a negative relationship with human answers with a coefficient of -0.25 (95% CI -0.31, -0.20) and an R 2 value of 0.066.",
    "No model showed coefficients even close to the human-to-human coefficient of 0.93 (95% CI 0.90, 0.96) with an R 2 value of 0.858.",
    "Finally, we asked the model whether the red agent would have succeeded in reaching the star, had the blue agent not been there.",
    "We show the square root of the R 2 for the Bayesian linear mixed effects regression with 95% percentiles in Fig. 6d.",
    "Interestingly, the results here flip, with Otter now showing a stronger negative relationship with a coefficient of -0.40 (95% CI -0.47, -0.33) and an R 2 value of 0.161 (this makes sense, since this task is essentially a counterfactual simulation question similar to Fig. 4d, where Otter already showed a negative relation to human judgements)."
  ]
}